<doc id="1021711" wikidata="Q1022295" url="?curid=1021711" title="Salem, Sweden">
<text>Salem () is the seat of Salem Municipality, Stockholm County, Sweden. Statistically it is a part of the bimunicipal contiguously built-up Tumba urban area.

In 2005, Salem had a population of 14,171. The number of inhabitants increased to ca. 16,000 in 2008, and to almost 17,000 in 2020 .

==Notable people==
 
*Edoff Andersson (1902–1934), Swedish politician and trade unionist

